The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Wockhardt rating blow
                                                                                                               Wockhardt rating blow
          
	New Delhi, April 3 (PTI): Rating agency Fitch has downgraded drug firm Wockhardt following the companys announcement of debt restructuring.        
	Crisil has also downgraded the rating of the short-term debt programme of the drug maker following a default by Wockhardt in interest payment on a loan. Fitch downgraded Wockhardts long-term rating to B from BBB. A B rating signifies high default risk. The rating follows Wockhardts announcement of a debt restructuring programme, Fitch said.                                                                                                                                        
